<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4551642>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Fig. 5. The anterior face of the proleg and mesoleg of a male Hypocryphalus dilutus (specimen 21 on tree).The mesofemoral spine is a unique character of H. dilutus. (A) Protibia with spatula shaped setae. (B) Mesofemur with spine. Photograph taken at approx. 200× magnification." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4551642/files/figure.png" .

